@startuml
title Account Invitation - Secure Provisioning Flow
autonumber
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAF7
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #9A8700

actor "Director general" as Director
participant "React accounts panel" as UI
participant "Security middleware\nCSRF + session + RBAC + Zod" as Security
participant AcademicController as Controller
participant AcademicService as Service
participant AccessPolicy as Policy
participant EmailService as Email
participant "SMTP provider\nMailpit in staging" as SMTP
database PostgreSQL as DB
participant AuditService as Audit

Director -> UI: Enter name, email, role, branch and profile data
UI -> Security: POST /api/v1/users + CSRF cookie/header
Security -> Security: validate active GeneralDirector/Admin session
Security -> Security: validate normalized input and allowed role
Security -> Controller: createUser(actor, command)
Controller -> Service: createAcademicUser(actor, command)
Service -> Policy: assertActorCanCreateRole(actor, role)
Policy -> DB: validate branch and role prerequisites
Service -> Service: generate cryptographically random temporary password
Service -> Service: hash temporary password
Service -> DB: transaction: create inactive user\n+ Student/Teacher profile + branch access
Service -> Email: sendAccessInvitation(name, email, password, role)
Email -> SMTP: branded HTML + text message\nyellow, gray and white

alt SMTP accepted the message
  SMTP --> Email: messageId / accepted recipient
  Email --> Service: delivery status sent
  Service -> DB: activate user/profile; mustChangePassword=true
  Service -> Audit: ACCOUNT_INVITATION_SENT
  Audit -> DB: append metadata without password
  Service --> Controller: public user + recipient + sent status
  Controller --> UI: 201 confirmation (no temporary password)
  UI --> Director: "Invitation sent to email"
else SMTP failure
  SMTP --> Email: delivery error
  Email --> Service: exception
  Service -> DB: keep account inactive
  Service -> Audit: ACCOUNT_INVITATION_FAILED
  Service --> UI: controlled error; retry is available
end

note right of UI
The director never sees or copies the temporary password.
Only the recipient receives it with first-login instructions.
end note
@enduml
